Alphonse CAPONE, Otherwise Known as Al Brown, v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 4553. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. June 20, 1932. See, also, 56 F.(2d) 927. William F. Waugh, of Chicago, 111., for appellant. George E. Q. Johnson, U. S. Atty., of Chicago, 111.

Before ALSCHULER, EVANS, and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellant, it is now here ordered and adjudged by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, and that the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
